Information Extraction is the process of automatically identifying and extracting structured information from unstructured text data. The goal is to transform raw text into meaningful data that can be easily analyzed and used in various applications. Named Entity Recognition (NER) and Relation Extraction are two common tasks in Information Extraction.

Named Entity Recognition involves identifying and classifying named entities such as people, organizations, locations, and other domain-specific concepts. Relation Extraction involves identifying and extracting relationships between entities.

